                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/9138: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-27T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 27, 1927—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 27—7:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>680. 1. Following from American consul at Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“101. June 25, 10 a.m. Steamer <hi rend="italic">Chilai</hi> of the
                            Yangtze Rapids Company bound up was fired upon by rifle fire near Ichang
                            June 22nd and one Chinese passenger killed and one seriously wounded.
                            Have lodged protest with Chinese authorities.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>2. I am informed that the Yangtze Rapids Company is attempting to resume
                    navigation between Ichang and Chungking in spite of my strong advice to the
                    contrary and statement that resumption of operations on the Upper Yangtze is
                    entirely at owner’s risk.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
